2026-07-07 — BUGFIX: logged-in user routed to profile-setup on cold restart
  What: On app restart a signed-in user was sent to the onboarding wizard
    (04 Complete your profile) instead of Discover. Root cause: AuthController
    .build() restored the persisted Supabase session but never loaded the
    user's profiles.profile_complete flag, so it defaulted to false — the
    router then saw signedIn && !profileComplete and forced onboarding. The
    flag was only fetched on a fresh signIn(), never on session restore.
  Fix (lib/features/auth/auth_controller.dart):
    - Added AuthState.bootstrapped (false until the initial session-restore +
      profile_complete fetch resolves).
    - build() now kicks off _bootstrapSession(userId) to fetch profile_complete
      for a restored session, then flips bootstrapped=true.
    - Auth-state-change stream handling extracted to _onAuthEvent(): refetches
      profile_complete on a genuinely new user id (OAuth / out-of-band session),
      preserves it across routine token refreshes, and clears it on sign-out.
    - signIn/signUp/signOut now also set bootstrapped=true.
  Fix (lib/core/router/router_guards.dart): redirect() returns null (no
    redirect) while !bootstrapped, so the guard can't force onboarding before
    the real profile-complete state is known; router re-runs on the flip.
  Result: flutter analyze on both files → No issues found. Behavior: logged-in
    user → Discover; logged-out user → /auth. Not driven on emulator this
    session — recommend a flutter run cold-restart walkthrough (login, kill,
    relaunch → lands on Discover).
