  User provided 16 screenshots (app doctumant/old app ss/onboring_screens/)
  and asked for pixel-parity, explicitly separate from the earlier field/
  logic diff list already produced this session. Also asked to change the
  app's default theme from following system/OS brightness to always
  defaulting to LIGHT (screenshots + bug report showed the app opening in
  dark mode because the test device's OS was in dark mode).

  0) DEFAULT THEME FIX - core/theme/theme_mode_controller.dart:
    - build() now returns ThemeMode.light instead of ThemeMode.system.
    - _load() no longer has a 'system' branch in its saved-pref switch -
      only 'dark' maps to dark, everything else (including no saved pref)
      is light. ThemeMode.system as an enum value still technically exists
      in Flutter but this controller never emits it anymore.
    - features/settings/settings_screen.dart _appearanceCard(): removed the
      now-dead `themeMode == ThemeMode.system && platformBrightnessOf(...)`
      branch from the isDark calculation - simplified to
      `themeMode == ThemeMode.dark`.

  1) SHARED WIDGETS (features/onboarding/onboarding_widgets.dart, NEW):
    - FieldLabel - bold black label above a field (old app's convention
      throughout onboarding; matches the Auth screen's Phase-1 style,
      which onboarding had never been updated to use).
    - DropdownSheetField - the old app's "tap to select..." control: an
      outlined box that expands an inline white rounded options list below
      it (not a modal), each row optionally emoji-suffixed, selected row
      highlighted solid gold. When `removable: true` and a value is
      selected, renders as a solid pink pill with a white X instead (matches
      the old app's post-selection look on marital-status/orientation/
      interested-in).
    - WarningBanner - the amber "exact birthday" warning box under Step 1's
      date field.

  2) STEP 1 - "About You" (features/onboarding/profile_setup_screen.dart,
     REWRITTEN top to bottom):
    - Added the silhouette-icon-style header (emoji instead of a photo
      placeholder graphic, since no such asset exists - close enough to the
      old app's icon in spirit without fabricating a bespoke illustration
      asset).
    - Birthday field: on selection, shows a separate pink pill badge to the
