      target with camera icon, then 3 small square thumbnails below with
      green border + green "Verified" caption once filled and a red X badge
      to remove/redo a slot.
    - The old flow's "avatar is optional, gallery is optional" framing is
      gone entirely - all 3 photos block Next until uploaded
      (_validateStep case 1).

  4) STEP 3 - "Your Location" (was: merged into the last step alongside a
     manual Country dropdown + City text field; now: its OWN standalone
     step, GPS-only, no manual fields at all - matches the old app exactly):
    - Large pin emoji header, "Your Location" / "We use your device location
      to find people near you." copy verbatim.
    - Single full-width pill button cycling through 3 visual states:
      outlined "Use My Current Location" -> filled amber "Detecting..." (via
      the REAL geolocator call added last session, unchanged) -> filled gold
      "Update My Location" once captured.
    - Result renders as a white card below the button: pin icon + bold
      label + gray circular X to clear.
    - HONEST GAP, flagged in code comments: the old app's result shows
      "Kabianga ward, Kenya" (a real reverse-geocoded place name). No
      reverse-geocoding service is wired anywhere in this app - faking a
      ward/city name from raw coordinates would violate the project's
      "never fake data" rule that's been enforced everywhere else this
      whole UI-parity effort. The result card instead shows the raw
      lat/lng coordinates (e.g. "-0.3667, 35.2833") until a real geocoding
