[2026-07-11] FIX: Discover card - action row + photo rail didn't match the old app
  User sent a screenshot that turned out to be the OLD APP'S OWN reference
  image (not our app) and asked me to compare our code against it directly
  rather than eyeball a claimed bug - good instinct, since the button order/
  colors already matched and there was nothing wrong to "see". Read the full
  discover_screen.dart source and diffed it precisely against
  IMG-20260709-WA0034.jpg / WA0050.jpg. Found 2 real, code-verifiable
  layout differences:
    1. Action row (X/star/chat/heart) was a SEPARATE sibling widget in the
       outer ListView, placed below the card with a 20px gap - rendering on
       the pink page background. In the reference the row sits INSIDE the
       black photo card, below the "Show more" chip, with the card's
       rounded black boundary still visible around it - the pink background
       only starts after the buttons.
    2. Multi-photo navigation was a vertical column of small numbered
       circles INSIDE the card's right edge. The reference instead shows a
       single translucent circular ">" arrow button vertically centered on
       the card's right edge (photo advance), with the numbered thumbnails
       (1/2/3, badge-numbered) floating OUTSIDE the card to its right, over
       the pink page background - not inside it at all.
  Fix - lib/features/discover/discover_screen.dart:
    - Removed the standalone _actionRow() call + its SizedBox(height: 20)
      gap from the outer ListView's children.
    - Moved _actionRow(p) to the end of the bottom-content Positioned
      Column inside the card's Stack (after "Show more"), so it now
      renders inside the card, matching the reference exactly.
    - Increased the card's AspectRatio from 3/4 (0.75) to 0.62 - taller,
      to fit the action row inside without cramping the photo/text content.
      (Old 3/4 was sized for a card with no buttons inside it.)
    - _card()'s return type changed from a single GestureDetector/
      AnimatedContainer tree to an outer Stack(clipBehavior: Clip.none)
      wrapping that same draggable card PLUS a new sibling Positioned
      (right: -8, top: 100) rendering the numbered-thumbnail column outside
      the card's clipped bounds - each thumbnail is now a 40px circular
      avatar with a small black-circle numbered badge (1/2/3) bottom-right,
      instead of the old small 30px plain-bordered circles that lived
      inside the card.
    - Inside the card, the old numbered-rail Positioned block was replaced
      with a single centered-right translucent circle (34px, chevronRight
      icon, black45 fill) that calls the same advancePhoto() as before.
    - Removed the GestureDetector(onTap: advancePhoto) that used to wrap
      the whole photo image (tap-anywhere-on-photo-to-advance) - now
      advancing is only via the dedicated arrow button or the thumbnail
      rail, matching the reference's single-button navigation pattern
      rather than a tap-anywhere affordance the reference doesn't show.
  Not changed (flagged, not fixed - a documented decision, not a bug): the
    "10h ago" last-active pill visible in the reference is still
    deliberately omitted - no user_presence.last_seen data exists to back
    it, and fabricating a value would violate the "never fake data" rule
    enforced everywhere else this session. Same for "Approx" GPS-accuracy
    badge (no accuracy field anywhere). Both remain [Phase 2 data gap]
    comments in the code, unchanged by this fix.
  Result: flutter analyze clean on the file and project-wide (same 4 pre-
    existing-style info lints, unrelated). flutter test green (2). flutter
    build apk --debug --dart-define=... -> SUCCESS, verified by extracting
    kernel_blob.bin and confirming the Supabase URL is embedded (per the
    black-screen-APK lesson from the prior session). NOT run on-device -
